LIDIF 0.1.0
  • Reference

    Preparing data for LIDIF function.

    prepare_data.Rd

    The function prepare your raw data to fit into LIDIF model.

    Usage

    prepare_data(X, Z)

    Arguments

    X

    A numeric matrix with columns corresponding to items. If the item is binary, please code it as 0/1; if the item is ordinal, please code it as integers starting from 1, e.g. 1,2,3. X can be missing at some columns but not the entire row.

    Z

    the matrix of exogenous variables. Z should not contain any missing data and should have the same number of rows as X. Please do not include intercept here.

    Value

    A list containing two elements.

    Examples

    items_matrix = cbind.data.frame("item1" = rbinom(100, 0,1),
                                "item2" = sample(c(1,2,3), size = 100, replace = TRUE))
covariates = cbind.data.frame("age" = runif(100, 10, 50),
                             "sex" = rbinom(100, 0, 1))
prepare_data(X = items_matrix, Z = covariates)
